The tiny radio, Chet cleverly concealed in my dog tag chain, was not the only special device I carried on my battle hardened, bronze body.  One of the beads contained a small nuclear power pack that operated my P-38 II... a can opener that I used against heavy armor when 17 lb HE warheads wouldn't work.  The frayed cord was a diversionary tactic to entice opponenents into the fatal belief that I was temporairly vulnerable by being unplugged.<br><br>
One bead contained an anti-spam device... another translated twenty six languages into Lakota (on the manual mode it would convert Infantry Sergeant's conversations into understandable English i.e.&quot;Huh?&quot; (I received your transmission) Whut? (Send your traffic) &quot;Duh?&quot; (Good copy) Yup! (will comply) etc.<br><br>
Other TOP SECRET beads, contained in my dog tag chain, are FOR MY NECK ONLY and will not be discussed except on a NEED TO KNOW basis.<br><br>
&quot;'toon Sergeant Duke knows a lot... I taught him everything he knows... I just didn't teach him everything I know!&quot;<br><br>
Mustang Two Four... Pop Smoke if you've got it... If not.. light up a pack of Salems...
